<br>
That's really unreasonable. I wouldn't feel right accepting that much for a few minutes of my time and my mana. I can meditate back 600 mana a lot faster than you can earn 400-1000pp (I guess unless you have the money just rolling in somehow). <br>
<br>
That's not to say I won't ever accept donation, especially if I have to travel a long distance to get there. Of course, if I'm rezzing a friend, or rezzing someone at the request of a friend, I won't accept anything. <br>
<br>
I like the idea of getting peridots as a donation. A cleric can never have too many, and even one or two helps out. The groups I've been in are pretty good about covering my costs, but it really is better to receive the actual gem than having to run and buy more all the time. <br>
<br>
Um, at the risk of being bombarded, I'll just say that if I have /roleplay off, there's a good chance that I'm not busy and I'll be happy to rez you. Bonus points if you ask nicely in Gnomish. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
