<br>
People have spoken of how they'd offer res' for free or a donation. Generally I've res'd for no charge, but donations are nice at times (done run-by buffs, heals etc, simply because it's nice for the young ones, and more importantly encourages them to be generous themselves).<br>
<br>
However, I can see why some Clerics have taken to charging a lot for a res. That is because of the cost of the higher end spells. Some of the spells I am looking for appear in the Bazaar with a 10k+ pp ticket attached. That's a lot of pp for a lot of people, myself included. So how else does one get those spells other than hunting for the critters that drop them and hope someone isn't farming them for the spells so they can sell them at inflated prices in the Bazaar? The only way is to charge high for casting spells, the same way Enchanters tend to. <br>
<br>
So it is greed, but not always the Cleric's greed.<br>
<br>
Still doesn't mean I'll be charging 100+ pp for a res, though.<br>
